commit 17a7b2e463f7b37fce1dd31b0f3e30be54f61155
Author: Artificer <w-mo3icdte-b867e4c93fc2@nexus.local>
Date:   Fri Apr 17 23:14:05 2026 +0000

    fix(spider): stop flicker and scroll-reset on rig-detail page

    The Spider rig-detail view's 2 s poll was rebuilding the engine-detail
    panel and pipeline row wholesale and re-opening the SSE transcript on
    every tick, collapsing <details> blocks, yanking <pre> scroll, and
    slamming the session-log textarea back to the bottom.

    Decouple the poll path from the click path:

    - Engine detail now renders against a stable-id skeleton built once on
      selection; the new updateEngineDetail writes only into existing
      containers, so <details> open state and <pre> scroll survive polls.
    - SSE lifecycle moves out of the per-render path. ensureSessionStream
      reopens only when the tracked sessionId actually changes (engine
      switch, or pending → running), not on rig polls.
    - Chunk and transcript handlers now use the existing atBottom
      capture-mutate-restore pattern from the noStream fallback, so
      scroll is preserved when the user has scrolled away from the tail.
    - renderPipelineInto switches to a keyed in-place update indexed by
      engine.id; the common "order unchanged" case patches badges in place.
    - /api/session/show is now requested once per engine (gated on a
      transition into 'completed'), not on every 2 s poll.

    Tests in spider-ui.test.ts are extended with regex assertions that
    lock in the new structure: updateEngineDetail exists; the poll path
    does not call showEngineDetail; chunk/transcript handlers contain
    atBottom; the pipeline renderer has a keyed-update path; the cost
    fetch is gated on engine status transition.

